title: Police seeking four N Korean suspects
text:
More 
Police are seeking four more North Korean suspects in relations to the murder of Kim Jong-nam, the older half-brother of North Korean ruler Kim Jong-un. 
Deputy inspector-general of police Noor Rashid Ibrahim said the four, all males, were believed to have left the country on Feb 13 - the day Jong-nam was murdered.
